{%- comment -%}
  Vertex AI Recommendations — v2 production slot renderer.
  Replaces the old placeholder snippet (which leaked preview chrome to live).

  ── Placement routing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Pass `placement:` to select the data source and layout class:

  | placement                | data source                                         |
  |--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
  | pdp_below_atc            | product.metafields.vertex.recs                      |
  | pdp_below_description    | product.metafields.vertex.recs (TAIL, offset 8 — bd 67d) |
  | cart_above_checkout      | cart.items[0].vertex.cart_recs → .recs fallback     |
  | home_below_hero          | customer.vertex.recommended_for_you → shop.trending |
  | cart_drawer_below_items  | cart.items[0].vertex.recs (v1 fallback)             |

  ── Arguments ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    placement  {String}   — slot identifier (required; defaults to 'unknown')
    product    {Product}  — anchor product (PDP placements)
    cart       {Cart}     — cart object (cart placements)
    customer   {Customer} — customer object (home RFY logged-in path)
    title      {String}   — section heading (required for customer-facing copy)
    subtitle   {String}   — section subheading (optional)
    rationale  {String}   — dev note shown in theme editor only (never on live)

  ── Safety gates ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  · Empty-state: if rec_products resolves to 0 items, the entire <section>
    is suppressed — no "No products" message renders on live.
  · Preview chrome (VERTEX badge + placement label) only renders when
    request.design_mode is true (theme editor). Never on preview-themed
    shop URLs or live.

  ── Performance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  · Zero new JS — CSS scroll-snap only.
  · Images: WebP <picture> + JPEG fallback, explicit width/height, lazy.
  · CSS: assets/vertex-recommendations.css (long-cached, ~8 KB).

  Phase 1b-γ.8 (2026-05-02): PR-1 universal foundation.
  See task-1-recommendations.md for PR sequencing + open questions.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign placement    = placement | default: 'unknown'
  assign rec_title    = title     | default: 'You might also like'
  assign rec_subtitle = subtitle  | default: ''

  assign rec_products = ''
  assign rec_source   = 'placeholder'
  assign rec_offset   = 0
  assign rec_limit    = 8

  case placement
    when 'pdp_below_atc'
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    when 'pdp_below_description'
      comment
        bd 67d (2026-07-18 audit): this placement read product.metafields.vertex.similar,
        which NO precompute writer ever writes (the similar model has no serving path),
        so it ALWAYS fell through to the sample:4 random-products fallback below — a prime
        PDP surface showing pseudo-random items on every product page. Re-point at the
        REAL FBT recs and show the TAIL (ranks 9-12) so it never duplicates the "Complete
        Your Routine" rail above (which renders the top 8). Products with <9 recs render
        nothing here and the section self-suppresses (empty rail_html check below) rather
        than showing random. Also lets us skip the $80-160 similar-model tune (bd 6hu).
      endcomment
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_offset   = 8
        assign rec_limit    = 4
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield_recs_tail'
      endif

    when 'cart_above_checkout'
      if cart and cart.items.first
        if cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.cart_recs
          assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.cart_recs.value
          assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
        elsif cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs
          assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
          assign rec_source   = 'metafield_fallback'
        endif
      endif

    when 'home_below_hero'
      if customer and customer.metafields.vertex.recommended_for_you
        assign rec_products = customer.metafields.vertex.recommended_for_you.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      elsif shop.metafields.vertex.homepage_trending
        comment
          Precompute writes shop.metafields.vertex.homepage_trending (NOT
          .trending) — confirmed against precompute/main.py:206-214.
        endcomment
        assign rec_products = shop.metafields.vertex.homepage_trending.value
        assign rec_source   = 'trending'
      endif

    when 'cart_drawer_below_items'
      if cart and cart.items.first and cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = cart.items.first.product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif

    else
      if product and product.metafields.vertex.recs
        assign rec_products = product.metafields.vertex.recs.value
        assign rec_source   = 'metafield'
      endif
  endcase

  comment
    Fallback to sample products so the slot is always visually populated,
    even when the precompute model hasn't written its metafield yet (or
    the metafield is empty / all handles failed to resolve). Two failure
    modes both need this fallback:
      • metafield missing entirely → rec_products is empty string ('')
      • metafield present but empty array → rec_products is [] (truthy
        in Liquid, so `unless rec_products` wouldn't fire)
    Hence the explicit size check, not just truthiness.
  endcomment
  assign rec_products_size = rec_products.size | default: 0
  if rec_products_size == 0
    for col in collections
      if col.products.size >= 4
        assign rec_products = col.products | sample: 4
        assign rec_source   = 'fallback_sample'
        break
      endif
    endfor
  endif

  assign card_count = rec_products.size | default: 0
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  Pre-render the rail into a buffer so we can detect whether ANY card
  actually rendered (avoids "header-with-no-cards" when every metafield
  handle resolves to a deleted/unpublished product).

  Two iteration shapes:
  1. Sample-fallback path → rec_products is a list of Shopify Product
     objects (from `collections | sample: 4`). entry.url is set.
  2. Metafield path → rec_products is a parsed JSON array of dicts
     {id, handle, vendor, score, final_score, margin_pct} written by
     precompute (type: "json", not list.product_reference). entry.url
     is nil; we resolve via all_products[entry.handle].
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  J11 S22 (bd 2i8b.76, web-team 2026-06-11): render-time exclusion guard.
  Recommendations must never show:
  - out-of-stock products (available == false — observed sold-out recs live),
  - freebies / promo SKUs (observed: "» FREE ... (100% off)" at ₱0 in the
    drawer rail) — detected by zero price, a leading "»", or "% off" in the
    title (plain "Free"/"-Free" words like "Sulfate-Free" do NOT match),
  - Backbar / salon-professional SKUs — vendor contains "Backbar" or tagged
    "bb exclusive" / "hm salon professional" (convention verified live via
    /products/<handle>.js on a Backbar product).
  This is the safety net at render time; the same exclusions belong upstream
  in the hairmnl-vertex precompute so metafields stop carrying these SKUs.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign vx_excluded_handles = shop.metafields.vertex.excluded_handles.value -%}
{%- comment -%}
  J16 S10/S11 (bd 2i8b.77, web-team 2026-06-16): never recommend a product that's
  already in the cart (FBT recs are anchored on the first cart item, so the item
  itself + its cart-mates surfaced in the drawer/cart rails). Build a delimited
  set of cart line-item handles; the loop skips any rec whose handle is in it.
  Render-time only — the precompute engine can't know the live cart.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign vx_cart_handles = '' -%}
{%- if cart and cart.item_count > 0 -%}
  {%- for li in cart.items -%}
    {%- assign vx_cart_handles = vx_cart_handles | append: '|' | append: li.product.handle | append: '|' -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- capture rail_html -%}
  {%- for entry in rec_products limit: rec_limit offset: rec_offset -%}
    {%- assign rec_p = nil -%}
    {%- if entry.url -%}
      {%- assign rec_p = entry -%}
    {%- else -%}
      {%- assign resolved = all_products[entry.handle] -%}
      {%- if resolved and resolved.handle != blank -%}
        {%- assign rec_p = resolved -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endif -%}
    {%- if rec_p -%}
      {%- assign rec_skip = false -%}
      {%- unless rec_p.available -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endunless -%}
      {%- if rec_p.price == 0 -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- assign rec_title_head = rec_p.title | strip | slice: 0, 1 -%}
      {%- if rec_title_head == '»' or rec_p.title contains '% off' or rec_p.title contains '% OFF' -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- if rec_p.vendor contains 'Backbar' or rec_p.vendor contains 'backbar' -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- if rec_p.tags contains 'bb exclusive' or rec_p.tags contains 'hm salon professional' -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- comment -%} Layer 3 of the engine's exclude system (precompute/exclude_lookup.py):
          the operator-managed Google-Sheet exclude list, mirrored to
          shop.metafields.vertex.excluded_handles every 15 min. This consult was
          designed-in but never wired into the theme widget until J11 S22. {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if vx_excluded_handles and vx_excluded_handles contains rec_p.handle -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- comment -%} J16 S10/S11: skip products already in the cart. {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if vx_cart_handles != '' -%}
        {%- capture rec_cart_needle -%}|{{ rec_p.handle }}|{%- endcapture -%}
        {%- if vx_cart_handles contains rec_cart_needle -%}{%- assign rec_skip = true -%}{%- endif -%}
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- unless rec_skip -%}
        {%- render 'vertex-rec-card', product: rec_p, placement: placement -%}
      {%- endunless -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Empty-state gate: suppress the entire section if EITHER (a) no products
  in the source list, OR (b) every product failed to resolve. Both states
  are treated identically — render nothing.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign rail_trimmed = rail_html | strip -%}
{%- if card_count == 0 or rail_trimmed == '' -%}{%- else -%}

<section
  class="vrec-slot vrec-slot--{{ placement }}"
  data-vertex-placement="{{ placement }}"
  data-vertex-anchor="{% if product %}{{ product.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-product-id="{% if product %}{{ product.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-vertex-source="{{ rec_source }}"
  aria-labelledby="vrec-title-{{ placement }}"
>
  <header class="vrec-slot__header">
    {%- comment -%}
      Use the theme's existing h2--body section-header__title classes so
      the title font + size match every other section on HairMNL
      (collection sliders, "Best Sellers", etc). The mockup's custom
      Cormorant Garamond was visually inconsistent with the live site.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <h2 id="vrec-title-{{ placement }}"
        class="h2--body section-header__title vrec-slot__title">{{ rec_title }}</h2>
    {%- if rec_subtitle != '' -%}
      <p class="vrec-slot__subtitle">{{ rec_subtitle }}</p>
    {%- endif -%}
  </header>

  <div class="vrec-slot__nav-wrap">
    <button type="button"
            class="vrec-slot__nav vrec-slot__nav--prev"
            aria-label="Scroll recommendations left"
            disabled>&lsaquo;</button>
    <div class="vrec-slot__rail" role="list">
      {{ rail_html }}
    </div>
    <button type="button"
            class="vrec-slot__nav vrec-slot__nav--next"
            aria-label="Scroll recommendations right">&rsaquo;</button>
  </div>
</section>

{%- comment -%}
  Inline init for the rail nav buttons. Scoped to this slot only via
  document.currentScript.closest('.vrec-slot'); idempotent via the
  data-vrec-init flag. ~25 lines net JS — needed because the team
  flagged "no buttons to navigate the sliders" on the preview theme.

  Uses scrollBy({behavior:'smooth'}) which scroll-snaps to the next
  card. The disabled state on the buttons updates from a scroll
  listener so the prev arrow disappears at the start and the next
  arrow disappears at the end.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  (function () {
    var script = document.currentScript;
    var slot = script && script.previousElementSibling;
    while (slot && !(slot.classList && slot.classList.contains('vrec-slot'))) {
      slot = slot.previousElementSibling;
    }
    if (!slot || slot.dataset.vrecInit) return;
    slot.dataset.vrecInit = '1';
    var rail = slot.querySelector('.vrec-slot__rail');
    var prev = slot.querySelector('.vrec-slot__nav--prev');
    var next = slot.querySelector('.vrec-slot__nav--next');
    if (!rail || !prev || !next) return;
    function step() {
      var card = rail.querySelector('.vrec-card');
      return card ? card.offsetWidth + 20 : 200;
    }
    function syncDisabled() {
      var atStart = rail.scrollLeft <= 1;
      var atEnd = rail.scrollLeft + rail.clientWidth >= rail.scrollWidth - 1;
      prev.toggleAttribute('disabled', atStart);
      next.toggleAttribute('disabled', atEnd);
    }
    prev.addEventListener('click', function () {
      rail.scrollBy({ left: -step(), behavior: 'smooth' });
    });
    next.addEventListener('click', function () {
      rail.scrollBy({ left: step(), behavior: 'smooth' });
    });
    rail.addEventListener('scroll', syncDisabled, { passive: true });
    window.addEventListener('resize', syncDisabled);
    syncDisabled();
  })();
</script>

{%- endif -%}
